<div id='wikitext'>
<p>Scrolling is triggered on about 1px border, which is not enough (especialy in windowed mode). Shoud be at least 5 px and maybe progresivelly regulate speed.
</p><p class='vspace'></p>
<ul><li><span style='color: green;' >(Jave27) - That code is in <code>playfield.cxx</code> and I'm working on it.</span>
</li></ul><p class='vspace'></p><p><a class='urllink' href='http://www.cmhousing.net/pingus/wiki/uploads/Main/gradient_autoscroll.diff' rel='nofollow'>Attach:gradient_autoscroll.diff</a> - patch to improve it.
</p><p class='vspace'></p>
<p>Actually, I have a patch which does something similar, but I was not satisfied. When the border is relatively thin, than progressing speed is not convenient and when it is thick, than it scrolls when you try to click on action buttons. - <a class='createlinktext' href='../Profiles/TomáBláha@action=edit'>Tomáš Bláha</a><a 
    class='createlink' href='../Profiles/TomáBláha@action=edit'>?</a> October 05, 2005, at 03:59 AM
</p>
</div>

